OL,3,CPossible changes to Jersey's 'archaic'
OL,4,Calcohol licensing law
OL,6,FJersey's alcohol licensing law could
OL,7,Fbe updated, depending on the outcome
OL,8,Fof a consultation into the matter.
OL,10,FThe law dates back to 1974 and
OL,11,Fsubjects hospitality businesses to
OL,12,Fbureaucracy and red tape controlled -
OL,13,Fnot by elected politicians - but by
OL,14,Fthe Royal Court.
OL,16,FIt also prevents promotions on
OL,17,Falcoholic drinks, such as two-for-ones
OL,18,Fand 'happy hours', and sets strict
OL,19,Frules about opening hours.
