OL,3,CPossible changes to Jersey's 'archaic'
OL,4,Calcohol licensing law
OL,6,FThe news of a consultation on the law
OL,7,Ffollows the closure of a number of
OL,8,Fclubs in recent months, including
OL,9,FHavana, Ce Soir and RoJo.
OL,11,FWhat is the current law in Jersey?
OL,13,FThe sale of alcohol is governed by the
OL,14,FLicensing Jersey Law 1974 which means:
OL,16,FLindsay Ash, a former assistant
OL,17,Ftreasury minister, says: "Considering
OL,18,Fwe are a capitalist society and Jersey
OL,19,Fis a finance centre, to have such a
OL,20,Fnon-competitive environment just
OL,21,Fdefies logic.
